<h2 id=''>The Drunken Scotsman
</h2>
</p><p>Well a Scotsman clad in kilt 
<br>left a bar one evening fair
<br>And one could tell by how he walked 
<br>that he’d drunk more than his share
<br>He fumbled round until he could 
<br>no longer keep his feet
<br>Then he stumbled off into the grass 
<br>to sleep beside the street
<br>
</p><p><i>Ring ding diddle diddle I de oh 
</i><br><i>ring di diddly I oh
</i><br><i>He stumbled off into the grass 
</i><br><i>to sleep beside the street
</i><br>
</p><p>About that time two young 
<br>and lovely girls just happened by
<br>And one says to the other 
<br>with a twinkle in her eye
<br>See young sleeping Scotsman 
<br>so strong and handsome built
<br>I wonder if it’s true what they 
<br>don’t wear beneath the kilt
<br>
</p><p><i>Ring ding diddle diddle I de oh 
