</i><br>
</p><p>Now the Scotsman woke to nature’s call 
<br>and stumbled toward the trees
<br>Behind a bush, he lifts his kilt 
<br>and gawks at what he sees
<br>And in a startled voice he says 
<br>to what’s before his eyes.
<br>O lad I don’t know where you been 
<br>but I see you won first prize
